import textwrap
from IPython.display import Markdown

def to_markdown(text):
  text = text.replace('â€¢', ' *')
  text = text.replace('**', '')
  return Markdown(textwrap.indent(text, '', predicate=lambda _: True)).data

#print(to_markdown("Greetings! As an AI research assistant named Cimplify, I'm here to help you with your research and questions. Here's a comprehensive list of different types of diseases classified into several categories:\n\n1. **Infectious Diseases:**\n\n   - Bacterial Infections: Caused by bacteria, such as pneumonia, tuberculosis, and strep throat.\n   - Viral Infections: Caused by viruses, such as influenza, measles, and AIDS.\n   - Fungal Infections: Caused by fungi, such as athlete's foot, ringworm, and candidiasis.\n   - Parasitic Infections: Caused by parasites, such as malaria, hookworm, and tapeworms.\n\n2. **Non-Infectious Diseases:**\n\n   - Cardiovascular Diseases: Diseases of the heart and blood vessels, such as heart attacks, strokes, and high blood pressure.\n   - Respiratory Diseases: Diseases affecting the lungs and airways, such as asthma, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), and lung cancer.\n   - Digestive Diseases: Diseases affecting the digestive system, such as Crohn's disease, ulcerative colitis, and liver cirrhosis.\n   - Metabolic Diseases: Diseases affecting metabolism, such as diabetes, thyroid disorders, and obesity.\n   - Neurological Diseases: Diseases affecting the brain and nervous system, such as Alzheimer's disease, Parkinson's disease, and multiple sclerosis.\n   - Musculoskeletal Diseases: Diseases affecting the bones, muscles, and joints, such as arthritis, osteoporosis, and fibromyalgia.\n   - Dermatological Diseases: Diseases affecting the skin, such as eczema, psoriasis, and skin cancer.\n\n3. **Genetic Diseases:**\n\n   - Single-gene Disorders: Caused by mutations in a single gene, such as cystic fibrosis, sickle cell anemia, and Huntington's disease.\n   - Chromosomal Disorders: Caused by abnormalities in the number or structure of chromosomes, such as Down syndrome, Turner syndrome, and Klinefelter syndrome.\n   - Multifactorial Genetic Disorders: Caused by a combination of genetic and environmental factors, such as heart disease, cancer, and diabetes.\n\n4. **Mental Health Disorders:**\n\n   - Mood Disorders: Disorders affecting mood, such as depression, bipolar disorder, and anxiety disorders.\n   - Psychotic Disorders: Disorders characterized by hallucinations, delusions, and disorganized thinking, such as schizophrenia.\n   - Personality Disorders: Disorders characterized by inflexible and unhealthy personality traits, such as antisocial personality disorder and borderline personality disorder.\n   - Eating Disorders: Disorders characterized by abnormal eating behaviors, such as anorexia nervosa, bulimia nervosa, and binge eating disorder.\n\n5. **Lifestyle-Related Diseases:**\n\n   - Cardiovascular Diseases: Can be influenced by lifestyle factors such as unhealthy diet, lack of physical activity, and smoking.\n   - Respiratory Diseases: Can be influenced by smoking, air pollution, and occupational exposures.\n   - Diabetes: Can be influenced by lifestyle factors such as unhealthy diet, physical inactivity, and obesity.\n   - Obesity: Can be influenced by lifestyle factors such as unhealthy diet, physical inactivity, and genetic predisposition.\n\n6. **Rare Diseases:**\n\n   - Rare diseases affect a small number of people and can be genetic, infectious, or caused by environmental factors. Examples include Gaucher disease, Pompe disease, and Huntington's disease.\n\nRemember that this is just a general categorization, and there are many other diseases that may not fit neatly into these categories. If you have specific questions about a particular disease, feel free to ask, and I'll do my best to provide you with detailed information. Stay healthy!"))